the figures in our manuscript. One of the 6 panels in Figure 2B which show radioactive PCR reactions assessing alternative splice insertions in <italic>Nrxn1</italic> was mistakenly taken from reactions performed for <italic>Nrxn2</italic>.</p><p>The experiments for <italic>Nrxn1, 2,</italic> and <italic>3</italic> were always performed in parallel and the relative distributions of <italic>Nrxn1</italic> and <italic>2</italic> splice variants detected with this method were very similar. We have replaced the mistaken panel to reflect the accurate data and the article has been corrected accordingly.</p><p>The corrected Figure 2 us shown here:<fig id="fig1" position="float"><graphic mime-subtype="postscript" mimetype="application" xlink:href="elife-28013-fig1-v1"/></fig></p><p>The originally published Figure 2 is also shown for reference:<fig id="fig2" position="float"><graphic mime-subtype="postscript" mimetype="application" xlink:href="elife-28013-fig2-v1"/></fig></p></body></article>